Reasoning: The sheet has three columns: Store Name (A), City (B), and a column C that should contain a formula indicating whether the City is mentioned at the end of the Store Name (no extra text after the city). The desired logic is: TRUE if the Store Name ends with the City (ignoring leading/trailing spaces), otherwise FALSE. We'll write a formula in column C for every data row that implements this check: =IF(RIGHT(TRIM(A2),LEN(B2))=B2,TRUE,FALSE). After writing the formulas, we'll recalculate the workbook so that the formulas evaluate, then reload the file with data_only=True to read the computed TRUE/FALSE values. Based on those values we'll set the fill color of column C cells: green (FF00B050) for TRUE and red (FFFF0000) for FALSE, matching the existing example. We'll preserve all existing fonts and other formatting by only modifying column C values and fills. Finally, we'll save the workbook to the output directory and submit the path.
Code:
```repl
import os
import openpyxl
from openpyxl.styles import PatternFill
from openpyxl.utils import get_column_letter

# Paths
input_path = '/sandbox/input/input_spreadsheet/1_51586_init.xlsx'
output_dir = '/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet'
output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, '1_51586_init.xlsx')

# Ensure output directory exists
os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)

# Load workbook (preserve existing formatting)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path)
ws = wb[wb.sheetnames[0]]  # assume first sheet is the target

max_row = ws.max_row
max_col = ws.max_column

# Write formula into column C for each data row (starting at row 2)
for r in range(2, max_row + 1):
    # Build formula string for this row
    formula = f"=IF(RIGHT(TRIM(A{r}),LEN(B{r}))=B{r},TRUE,FALSE)"
    ws.cell(row=r, column=3, value=formula)  # column 3 = C

# Save workbook with formulas
wb.save(output_path)

# Recalculate formulas using LibreOffice (async tool)
await recalculate(output_path)

# Reload workbook with data_only to read evaluated values
wb_eval = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws_eval = wb_eval[wb_eval.sheetnames[0]]

# Define fills
fill_green = PatternFill(start_color="FF00B050", end_color="FF00B050", fill_type="solid")
fill_red   = PatternFill(start_color="FFFF0000", end_color="FFFF0000", fill_type="solid")

# Apply fill colors based on evaluated TRUE/FALSE in column C
for r in range(2, ws_eval.max_row + 1):
    cell = ws_eval.cell(row=r, column=3)
    # Determine fill based on Boolean value (True/False) or any non-True as False
    if cell.value is True:
        ws.cell(row=r, column=3).fill = fill_green
    else:
        ws.cell(row=r, column=3).fill = fill_red

# Save final workbook (preserving formulas and new fills)
wb.save(output_path)

print('Processing complete. Output saved to', output_path)
```
